<doc id="1235147" wikidata="Q173597" url="?curid=1235147" title="Óscar González (racing driver)">
<text>Óscar Mario &quot;Bocha&quot; González Alonso (10 November 1923 – 5 November 2006) was a racing driver from Uruguay.

González participated in one Formula One Grand Prix, the 1956 Argentine Grand Prix on 22 January 1956, finishing sixth in a shared drive with countryman Alberto Uría. He scored no championship points.

